        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 18 at 9:43AM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>HAZARDS...A band of heavy snow accompanied by winds of up to 35 mph
which will rapidly reduce visibility to less than a half of a mile.

LOCATION AND MOVEMENT...At 942 AM MDT, a band of heavy snow was near
Hayden, or 12 miles east of Craig moving east at 30 MPH.

THIS BAND OF HEAVY SNOW WILL BE NEAR...
Hayden around 950 AM MDT.
Steamboat Springs around 1010 AM MDT.

This includes U.S. Highway 40 in Colorado between mile markers 98 and
130.

SAFETY INFO...
Conditions can deteriorate rapidly in winter weather situations. Be
prepared for snow or ice covered roads. Slow down and allow extra
time to reach your destination.
</description>
